Oh come in, come in.

49
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:35,370
Now, this man here has just finished his national tour,

50
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:38,570
coming straight from the airport. Your most adored Sunbae,

51
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:40,150
Park Joon Young.

52
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,640
All right. Shall we begin?

53
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:14,980
Oh wait, wait, wait, wait.

54
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:21,520
First violins, in the very back, the final row.

55
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,540
Yes, you two.

56
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:32,040
Right now the violins are too loud so I think I'll have to take out a row.

57
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:37,280
You two won’t need to perform today, so go home.

58
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:39,210
And cello!

59
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:42,440
 Can’t you play a little more expressively? 

60
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:45,140
 It's molto espressivo. 

61
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:47,690
A high position.

62
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:53,610
Why are you still here?

63
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:14,810
What are you fidgeting around here for? I told you to go home!

64
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,330
That is—

65
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:26,960
I…

66
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:33,990
I practiced a lot for this.

67
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,220
What?

68
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:56,030
Couldn’t I perform together with you?

69
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:02,560
What’s your name?

70
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,330
It’s Chae Song Ah.

71
00:09:07,330 --> 00:09:09,850
No, no, no, no.

72
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:13,950
I don’t want your apologies. What’s your name? 
 (T/N: "Chae Song" and "sorry" sound similar.)

73
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,170
M-My name is—

74
00:09:20,210 --> 00:09:25,840
So, my name is— It’s Chae Song Ah, sir.

75
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,690
- Chae Song…
   - No! 

76
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:31,810
I asked for your name. Don’t you understand? “Name!"

77
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:49,720
Did I ask you to leave without reason?

78
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:53,170
The violin’s volume is too loud.

79
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:55,470
Are you the conductor?

80
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:06,910
Your positions here are ranked by performance, right?

81
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:11,440
Then you shouldn't have gotten last place!

82
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:27,610
Forgive me.

83
00:10:27,610 --> 00:10:29,820
My hand slipped.

84
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,300
Sit down. Just play.

85
00:11:12,690 --> 00:11:14,580
Let’s begin.

86
00:11:20,110 --> 00:11:22,710
No, wait, wait, wait, wait.

87
00:11:26,970 --> 00:11:29,510
This just won’t work. You...

88
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:31,270
get out.

89
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:35,100
Don’t come in for today’s performance.

90
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,000
Now everyone!

91
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,990
Smile.

92
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:30,690
 Hey Song Ah, I’m at the arts center! 

93
00:12:30,690 --> 00:12:33,000
 I’m here to see your performance! 

94
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,740
I’m here to buy some tickets.

95
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:45,450
I’m sorry, but we currently don’t have any more tickets remaining.

96
00:12:45,450 --> 00:12:47,410
Not even a single ticket?

97
00:12:47,410 --> 00:12:49,290
No.

98
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:52,250
Later when the performance starts, the stage will show up on the TV, right?

99
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,970
Yes, you can check it out then.

100
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:56,680
They show each member of the orchestra too, right?

101
00:12:56,680 --> 00:13:00,790
No, this is purely for monitoring purposes, so it will focus on the piano.

102
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:04,470
- F-Focus on the piano? 
 - Yes.

103
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:07,890
Thank you very much.

104
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:12,240
What the heck? Is Park Joon Young the only performer?

105
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:16,950
   

106
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:21,490
 They didn’t have any more tickets, so I thought I’d watch you from the lobby TV, but they only show the piano. 

107
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:24,030
 It looks like I won't be able to see you. 

108
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:33,270
 Did you say you're going to America after grad school? 

109
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,640
 Probably? 

110
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:39,130
 But about Song Ah Unni, what happens after she graduates? 

111
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:46,150
The heck if I knew. I’m sure she’ll figure it out.

112
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:48,320
If you’re so curious, go ask her yourself.

113
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:52,450
It’s okay. It feels awkward to ask her about stuff like that.

114
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:55,370
 The concert will begin in 10 minutes. 

115
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:57,780
 All members please standby for entrance. 

116
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:59,920
- Let’s go.
- Yeah.

117
