118
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:21,340
   

119
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,610
 Thank you for your letter and DVD. 

120
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:28,690
 Upon reviewing your materials, unfortunately, 

121
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:31,090
 I am unable to accept you into my studio 

122
00:14:31,090 --> 00:14:35,000
 for the Master of Music Degree at Daleson University. 

123
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:45,380
 The soloist and conductor will enter now. 

124
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:47,700
You may enter now.

125
00:16:58,020 --> 00:16:59,730
Hey, there.

126
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:02,810
If you want to see the stage,

127
00:17:02,810 --> 00:17:04,970
you can go over there.

128
00:17:42,090 --> 00:17:45,250
 I started to cry. 

129
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,710
 The music that spilled from him 

130
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:52,470
 burned so hot. 

131
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:57,220
 What’s contained within me 

132
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:01,990
 felt so small and pathetic in comparison. 

133
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:04,260
 I cried. 

134
00:18:13,190 --> 00:18:15,330
You should come with me to the reception area.

135
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:16,910
Even Mr. Lee came.

136
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:20,270
No, don’t worry about it.

137
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:24,420
I know when I’m not wanted.

138
00:18:24,420 --> 00:18:27,560
I already got tickets for the bus.

139
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:31,120
Yes, have a safe trip home. I’ll call you.

140
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,590
Okay.

141
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:34,900
But Joon Young…

142
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,810
your pay for this month’s performances…

143
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:42,190
Oh… you haven’t gotten them yet?

144
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,330
I’ll ask my company about it.

145
00:18:45,330 --> 00:18:47,940
I’m sorry, Son.

146
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:52,330
Even so, your father has changed a lot these days.

147
00:18:53,870 --> 00:18:56,740
I’m leaving now, okay?

148
00:18:56,740 --> 00:18:58,830
Stay safe!

149
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:05,680
Go in!

150
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:28,340
Oh, Unni!

151
00:19:28,340 --> 00:19:31,020
Why are you here? Didn’t you leave earlier?

152
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,850
Oh… t-that—

153
00:19:32,850 --> 00:19:37,870
Ah right. I meant to ask you about this earlier.

154
00:19:37,870 --> 00:19:39,630
Are you going to do the internship?

155
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:41,090
Huh?

156
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:44,320
Kyunghoo Cultural Foundation's summer internship.

157
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,800
Today's the last day to accept the spot.

158
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:49,380
I emailed them that I'm doing it.

159
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,980
I haven't yet.

160
00:19:52,980 --> 00:19:55,060
What? You haven’t yet?

161
00:19:55,440 --> 00:20:00,330
If you aren’t going to do it, it’d be better to reply now that you won’t.

162
00:20:02,570 --> 00:20:05,360
It’s not that I’m not doing it.

163
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:07,130
I just haven’t decided yet.

164
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:09,670
Oh… I see.

165
00:20:09,670 --> 00:20:13,820
Well, I’m going to use the restroom now. Goodbye.

166
00:20:25,380 --> 00:20:27,270
Oh, Min Seong, where are you?

167
00:20:27,270 --> 00:20:29,560
I’m at— Hmm?

168
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:31,220
One second.

169
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:33,460
Sorry, but could I take one more?

170
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:35,000
Yes.

171
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:45,120
Song Ah!

172
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:47,180
Thank you.

173
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:50,280
Congrats on your debut!

174
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,780
Just a moment.

175
00:20:53,780 --> 00:20:57,350
 Then you shouldn't have gotten last place! 

176
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:04,850
   

177
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:10,910
How was it? Did you do well?

178
00:21:10,910 --> 00:21:13,300
Good work today.

179
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:17,980
He told you good work!

180
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:21,860
Want to eat? You haven't eaten yet, right?

181
00:21:21,860 --> 00:21:24,160
Want me to buy you meat?

182
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:27,040
I'll buy.

183
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:31,850
I congratulate you on the 60th year anniversary

184
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:36,150
of the Seoryeong University School of Music.

185
00:21:40,490 --> 00:21:45,270
I think I have a special connection with Seoryeong University's School of Music.

186
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:49,330
Today's pianist, Park Joon Young,

187
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:52,670
studied here at Seoryeong's School of Music.

188
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:55,820
And my granddaughter

189
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:59,880
is a violinist who graduated from the same school.

190
00:22:00,550 --> 00:22:03,180
It's a shame Jung Kyung isn't here.

191
00:22:03,180 --> 00:22:06,830
If she's in America, will she even come back once a year?

192
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:11,900
 In this position, 

193
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,780
 I made a promise to myself. 

194
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:17,460
   

195
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:22,470
It's a shame. You did well in the past.

196
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:28,020
Well. It's time for me to think of my health.

197
00:22:28,020 --> 00:22:32,410
Don't you know? We're still 29.

198
00:22:32,410 --> 00:22:34,520
Ah, right.

199
00:22:36,020 --> 00:22:38,230
Surprise! It's a present.

200
00:22:38,230 --> 00:22:39,390
What's this?

201
00:22:39,390 --> 00:22:42,600
A calendar that starts on your birthday.

202
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,820
I made it.

203
00:22:46,820 --> 00:22:48,790
Thank you!

204
00:22:48,790 --> 00:22:51,220
   

205
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:57,540
Yoon Dong Yoon is the same as now.

206
00:22:58,370 --> 00:23:01,370
Yeah. You're right.

207
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:06,830
It's been years since we broke up after dating for just 100 days,

208
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:10,230
but why am I still fussing over Yoon Dong Yoon like this?

209
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:15,870
If you tell him that I still like him or whatever, you're dead.

210
00:23:15,870 --> 00:23:18,850
Why would I say that?

211
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,360
Cheers!

212
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:29,510
I heard you're taking a break this summer in Korea.

213
00:23:30,290 --> 00:23:32,950
I'm the Performance Arts Director of Korea's Philharmonic Orchestra.

214
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:37,320
What are your thoughts on joining me for next year's New Year Music Festival?

215
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:40,610
Thank you so much for the invitation,

216
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:43,390
but I'm not planning to perform this year.

217
00:23:43,390 --> 00:23:45,740
It seems like it'll be hard.

218
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:48,430
I heard you're doing a performance for Kyunghoo.

219
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:52,410
Well, that's something that came up a while ago.

220
00:23:52,410 --> 00:23:54,450
I'm sorry.

221
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:11,750
I still haven't decided whether to do that internship yet.

222
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:14,360
What? Why?

223
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:18,680
If I go to work, I feel like I won't have as much time to practice.

224
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:23,480
Hey. You can just practice on weekends or after work.

225
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:26,810
Still, you know what they say.

226
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:28,720
If I don't practice for one day, I'll notice.

227
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,820
If I don't practice for two days, my colleagues will notice.

228
00:24:30,820 --> 00:24:33,910
And if I don't practice for 3 days, the audience will notice.

229
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:37,840
Just think of it as gathering next semester's tuition.

230
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,330
Okay.

231
00:24:40,330 --> 00:24:43,720
When are they going to let you graduate, Min Seong?

232
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,340
I don't know.

233
00:24:45,340 --> 00:24:47,090
Why did I go to grad school?

234
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:50,600
Darn. I just had to like something like chemistry.

235
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:56,490
Me too. I just had to like something like music.

236
00:24:56,490 --> 00:24:59,260
Yeah. You're the problem here.

237
00:24:59,260 --> 00:25:02,090
You suddenly said you'd do violin,

238
00:25:02,090 --> 00:25:04,150
and wouldn't listen even if I told you not to.

239
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:06,040
Right?

240
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:11,160
Back then, the only person who supported me was CEO Yoon.

241
00:25:13,610 --> 00:25:16,580
It'll all work out. Don't worry.

242
00:25:16,580 --> 00:25:20,160
How do you know? Are you a fortune-teller?

243
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:26,360
Because you're my friend.

244
00:25:31,490 --> 00:25:34,470
Was my Song Ah touched?

245
00:25:34,470 --> 00:25:37,970
I'll go to the bathroom, so don't cry and stay here.

246
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:40,310
I'll be right back.

247
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:48,800
 What's this? 

248
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:51,160
Yoon Ah!

249
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:53,740
It's okay.

250
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:58,050
This is a violin.

251
00:25:58,050 --> 00:25:59,770
Violin?

252
00:25:59,770 --> 00:26:02,499
Yeah. Violin.

253
00:26:04,170 --> 00:26:05,830
Unni,

254
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:08,430
are you good at the violin?

255
00:26:11,150 --> 00:26:13,200
Are you good?

256
00:26:23,650 --> 00:26:28,120
I like to play. A lot.

257
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:35,300
I can drop you off on the way.

258
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:36,470
No, I can walk.

259
00:26:36,470 --> 00:26:38,260
- Really? 
 - Yes. Hurry and go.

260
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:40,000
Okay.

261
00:26:40,820 --> 00:26:42,610
Text me when you get home. I'll go then!

262
00:26:42,610 --> 00:26:45,280
- Okay, bye! 
 - Bye!

263
00:26:56,730 --> 00:26:59,020
   

264
00:26:59,020 --> 00:27:02,160
 Ah, Park Joon Young! 

265
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:04,660
 He said he's busy, so he can't do ours. 

